Analyze Multiple Data Model Objects Using Joins (Beta)

To explore and draw insights from multiple related data model object records simultaneously, join these objects in a single dashboard query. Direct Data for Data Cloud supports four types of joins on data model objects with defined relationships between them.

Say you want to compare sales order data with product and customer's annual income.

Create a query on the Sales Order DMO.
Click Manage Data Sources.
The Manage Data Sources window displays a list of related data sources.
Add the related Individual and Product DMOs to the query.
By default, the DMOs are joined using a left join.
Apply your changes.
Build your query on the joined DMOs in the dashboard lens.
title: Analyzing Multiple Data Sources Using Joins
